Calender Class

1. What is Calendar class in Java? Important Methods of Calendar?
-->Answer:

The Calendar class (java.util.Calendar) is a legacy class used to manipulate dates and times. It allows you to get, set, add, and compare dates.

Import:
    import java.util.Calendar;
    
    Create a Calendar object:
    
    Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();


    Important Methods :
| Method                        | Description                                   |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `getInstance()`               | Returns current date and time                 |
| `get(int field)`              | Gets a field value (year, month, day)         |
| `set(int field, int value)`   | Sets a field value                            |
| `add(int field, int amount)`  | Adds/subtracts time                           |
| `roll(int field, boolean up)` | Changes field without affecting larger fields |
| `getTime()`                   | Returns a Date object                         |
| `before()`                    | Checks if date is before another date         |
| `after()`                     | Checks if date is after another date          |





2. How to convert Calendar to LocalDateTime (Java 8+)?
-->Answer:
    
    Use toInstant() and ZoneId.
    
    import java.util.Calendar;
    import java.time.LocalDateTime;
    import java.time.ZoneId;
    
    public class Main {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();
    
            LocalDateTime ldt = LocalDateTime.ofInstant(
                    cal.toInstant(),
                    ZoneId.systemDefault());
    
            System.out.println(ldt);
        }
    }





3. How to get the current year, month, and day using Calendar?
-->Answer:

      Use the get() method.
      
      import java.util.Calendar;
      
      public class Main {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
              Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();
      
              int year = cal.get(Calendar.YEAR);
              int month = cal.get(Calendar.MONTH) + 1;
              int day = cal.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH);
      
              System.out.println("Year : " + year);
              System.out.println("Month: " + month);
              System.out.println("Day  : " + day);
          }
      }

Output (Example):

      Year : 2026
      Month: 7
      Day  : 24
      
      Note: Months start from 0, so add 1.





4. How do you roll a date forward or backward using Calendar?
-->Answer:

Use the roll() method.

Roll Forward
import java.util.Calendar;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();

        cal.roll(Calendar.DATE, true);

        System.out.println(cal.getTime());
    }
}
Roll Backward :
      import java.util.Calendar;
      
      public class Main {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
              Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();
      
              cal.roll(Calendar.DATE, false);
      
              System.out.println(cal.getTime());
          }
      }

Difference :
      add() changes higher fields if needed.
      roll() changes only the specified field.

Example:
      31 Jan + add(1 day)  -> 1 Feb
      31 Jan + roll(1 day) -> 1 Jan
